<TITLE> BRAC officials fined for pollution </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 22 (bdnews24.com)An environment court on Friday fined four BRAC officials Tk 12,000 each for pollution. Judge Fouzul Azim imposed the fines on Faisal Aziz, Adhir Chandra Saha, Md Rafiqul Islam and Mohammad Aliofficials of BRAC dairy and food projectafter they had pleaded guilty. The officials pledged that they would not repeat their offence in future. Inspector of the Department of Environment, Mahbubur Rahman filed a case on Aug 20, 2008 alleging that the organisation on Lakhsmipur road under Joydebpur upazila had been producing milk and dairy products without a liquid treatment plant and without environmental clearance. According to the case details, there was no result even after issuing a notice for polluting the area outside the factory. The notice was served on May 5 last year. BRAC established its dairy farm in 1998 and has a capacity of producing 10,000 litres of milk per hour. The factory at Gazipur produces powder milk since 2005, according to its website. bdnew
